## Custom Status Codes

The second argument to any route attribute sets the success status code. It defaults to `200`:

```php
#[Post('/users', 201)]
public function store(): UserResponse { /* ... */ }

#[Delete('/users/{id}', 204)]
public function destroy(int $id): void { /* ... */ }
```

## Route Parameters

Segments wrapped in `{}` are route parameters. They are extracted and injected into the controller method by name, cast to the declared type:

```php
#[Get('/posts/{postId}/comments/{commentId}')]
public function show(int $postId, int $commentId): array { /* ... */ }
```

Supported cast targets: `int`, `float`, `bool`, `string`.

